<subSubSection id="C3535486FF97F75EFF38FCF42395FC41" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF6070DFF97F75EFF38FCF42627FC39" blockId="12.[189,310,870,896]" box="[189,310,870,896]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="D0BEB061FF97F75EFF38FCF42627FC39" bold="true" box="[189,310,870,896]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF97F75EFF38FCF42627FC39" bold="true" box="[189,310,870,896]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF6070DFF97F75EFF38FC042395FC41" blockId="12.[189,1399,918,1016]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF97F75EFEB8FC0426D3FC09" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[317,450,918,944]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF97F75EFEB8FC0426D3FC09" box="[317,450,918,944]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the two bands on the forewing further apart, the cream white band on the hindwing underside is very narrow. Vesica of the aedeagus is shorter than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF97F75EFBC1FC2823D7FC6D" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[1092,1222,954,980]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF97F75EFBC1FC2823D7FC6D" box="[1092,1222,954,980]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. COI-barcode: the observed distance to the genetically most similar species (
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF97F75EFC14FC4C2302FC41" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[913,1043,990,1016]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF97F75EFC14FC4C2302FC41" box="[913,1043,990,1016]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is 3.3%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3535486FF97F75EFF38FBB224C5FBD0" box="[189,980,1056,1129]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
